{"TopicId":185489,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Set docking port active/unactive.","CreatedByName":"Aeroboi","CreatedById":186653,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-14T19:53:47Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Aeroboi","CreatedById":186653,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-14T19:53:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy idea was inspired by the inner lock mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022167015\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed8431148675\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/182833-131-171-inner-lock-lock-your-inner-parts/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:212px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe problem with stock docking ports is that if you decouple you require to be some distance away for the docking port to re-activate.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome people dislike this because you want to re-dock a mechanism, even with the new parts that may still be useful.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInstead, deactivate stock docking ports and then have a context menu option to re-activate the docking port at will with toggle on/off action group options.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-06-14T19:55:09Z\u0022 title=\u002206/14/2019 07:55  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJune 14, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Aeroboi\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-15T09:08:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s only 1/3 of a workaround, but\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Clamp-O-Tron_Shielded_Docking_Port.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002267.07\u0022 height=\u0022224\u0022 width=\u0022334\u0022 src=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/images/1/1a/Clamp-O-Tron_Shielded_Docking_Port.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso the distance to reactivate the port isn\u0027t that big?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}